						<div class="postbody">It processes pictures, not code ;-)
<br />
<br />Also re: NMI's being for sound, technically this isn't true.  You can probably run sound at any time, it not being critical to be timed in vertical blank, although it's usually a good idea to run it in NMI if you're doing weird stuff like split-screen madness.</div>

					
